Manchester United has announced that the club’s former midfielder, Darren Fletcher, has joined the Red Devils’ coaching staff. Man United disclosed this in a statement via its website on Monday. The statement read: “Manchester United is pleased to announce that Darren Fletcher will join the first-team coaching staff. “He has been coaching the Under-16s since October and will now join the first-team staff full-time.” Fletcher spent 20 years as a player at Old Trafford after coming through the Academy to make over 340 first team appearances for the club between 2003 and 2015. The 36-year-old Scottish won five Premier League titles, one FA Cup, two League Cups, the UEFA Champions League and the FIFA Club World Cup during his time as a Man United player.